"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-sport-sport-olympics-olympics-2024-final-medal-table-team-gb-b1175912.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 56, \"end\": 76, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Google Custom Search\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search.\", \"from\": 125, \"to\": 182, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"See our privacy policy for more information.\", \"from\": 183, \"to\": 227, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sport|Olympics  Team GBended the 2024Olympicswith a higher medal haul than they achieved in Tokyo three years ago.\", \"from\": 229, \"to\": 343, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 321, \"end\": 326, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.8294162455869244, \"rank\": 0.205667238426305, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bronzemedalspicked up on a dramatic final day at the Paris Games by Emily Campbell and Emma Finucane in weightlifting and the women's individual track cycling sprint respectively made it a brilliant finish to a memorable fortnight for Great Britain across The Channel.\", \"from\": 345, \"to\": 613, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 413, \"end\": 427, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emily_Campbell\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emily Campbell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emily_Campbell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emily_Campbell\"}, {\"begin\": 432, \"end\": 436, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\", \"score\": 0.9999225180928077, \"rank\": 5.5055780980264665e-05, \"text\": \"Emma\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\"}, {\"begin\": 580, \"end\": 593, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9998828689386445, \"rank\": 0.00011604520253517483, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was athird medal of the Olympics overall for Finucane, becoming the first British woman to achieve that feat since Mary Rand back in 1964.\", \"from\": 615, \"to\": 756, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 692, \"end\": 699, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999095095335729, \"rank\": 9.049722381663901e-05, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 738, \"end\": 742, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_African_rand\", \"score\": 0.999998536941054, \"rank\": 1.418446531957894e-06, \"text\": \"Rand\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_African_rand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_African_rand\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It meant that Britain achieved a final medal tally of 65 in Paris - one more than they managed in Tokyo in 2021, albeit with eight fewer golds.\", \"from\": 758, \"to\": 901, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 772, \"end\": 779, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9996521993728378, \"rank\": 0.00034792125850957345, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 818, \"end\": 823, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999995725375, \"rank\": 4.2746733790627167e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 856, \"end\": 861, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.8294162455869244, \"rank\": 0.205667238426305, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is the same number of medals overall that Team GB managed on home soil at London 2012 and two fewer than their stunning overseas haul in Rio de Janeiro in 2016.\", \"from\": 903, \"to\": 1066, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 948, \"end\": 955, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9998529616091623, \"rank\": 0.00014364758480322812, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 980, \"end\": 991, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999987362571, \"rank\": 1.2635823073080994e-09, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1043, \"end\": 1057, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8711743363747e-18, \"text\": \"Rio de Janeiro\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Such a collection was good enough for seventh place in the finalmedal table, their lowest finish since placing 10th at both Sydney 2000 and in Athens in 2004.\", \"from\": 1068, \"to\": 1226, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1211, \"end\": 1217, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.2980388691490906e-17, \"text\": \"Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"GB had finished fourth in the medal table in Tokyo and second in Rio, having been third in London and fourth at Beijing 2008.\", \"from\": 1228, \"to\": 1353, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1228, \"end\": 1230, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9966531895153642, \"rank\": 0.0033580492389869245, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 1273, \"end\": 1278, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.8294162455869244, \"rank\": 0.205667238426305, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 1293, \"end\": 1296, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999997367013, \"rank\": 2.631060646737259e-10, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1319, \"end\": 1325, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999998226485, \"rank\": 1.7152379120713093e-10, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Top spot once again belonged to the USA, who tie